                            <comment id="13463702" author="bvahdat" created="Wed, 26 Sep 2012 10:49:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Using WIN-XP I could not reproduce the problem and &lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/Validator-component-onException-tp5717756p5719718.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;asked the user&lt;/a&gt; to provide more details however got no response til now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also given the route the user has provided @ the forum I don&apos;t think file renaming will be invoked at all, because he makes use of &lt;tt&gt;DirectConsumer&lt;/tt&gt; and not &lt;tt&gt;FileConsumer&lt;/tt&gt; so there&apos;s no reason why &lt;tt&gt;FileUtil.renameFile&lt;/tt&gt; should kick-in!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13477964" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 17 Oct 2012 15:39:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There may be another route that is picking up files.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am adding some of the logic we have from xslt/xpath builders that also work with the various XML types / sources et all. And they have logic to ensure any input stream gets closed etc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
